messages.content: ComfyUI-Champ is an extension for ComfyUI that can generate images and videos using a stable diffusion model.
What models are required for ComfyUI-Champ?
ComfyUI-Champ requires the pretrained weights of base models such as StableDiffusion V1.5, sd-vae-ft-mse, and image_encoder.
Where can I download the pretrained weights for StableDiffusion V1.5?
The pretrained weights for StableDiffusion V1.5 can be downloaded from the Hugging Face model hub at [https://huggingface.co/runwayml/stable-diffusion-v1-5].
Where can I find the checkpoints for ComfyUI-Champ?
The checkpoints for ComfyUI-Champ are available on Google Drive at [https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1hZiOHG-qDf0Pj7tvfxC70JQ6wHUvUDoY].
How do I set the path for the ChampLoader node in ComfyUI-Champ?
The path for the ChampLoader node in ComfyUI-Champ should be set to the location where you have downloaded the pretrained weight of the base models.
What is the URL for the base workflow example for ComfyUI-Champ?
The base workflow example for ComfyUI-Champ can be found at [https://github.com/chaojie/ComfyUI-Champ/blob/main/wf.mp4].
